yoruba_text: Iwọ ha ń gbadura fun ẹmi mimọ ti o sì ń ṣọralati maṣe mú un banujẹ bi?
english_text: Do you pray for holy spirit andguard againstgrieving it?

yoruba_text: Bẹẹni, awọn ti wọn ń funni ni ibawi tabi atunṣe gbọdọṣọragidigidi lati maṣe lekoko lae.
english_text: Yes, those administering reproof or correction must be verycarefulnever to be harsh.

yoruba_text: Eeṣe ti alagba kan fi gbọdọṣọralati maṣe ṣe awọn ipinnu ti awọn ẹlomiran nilati ṣe funraawọn?
english_text: Why should an elder becarefulnot to make decisions that others should make themselves?

yoruba_text: Bawo ni a ṣe lèṣọrafun iwa-palapala ibalopọ takọtabo onibọriṣa?
english_text: How can weguard againstidolatrous sexual immorality?

yoruba_text: Awọn alagba gbọdọṣọraki wọn má tete maa binu tabi jẹ ẹni ti a ṣẹ si nito ri awọn ailera Kristian arakunrin ati arabinrin wọn.
english_text: Elders must becarefulnot to be easily annoyed or offended by the weaknesses of their Christian brothers and sisters.

yoruba_text: 8 Iduroṣinṣin ti Jehofa tun ń mu ki aṣọrafun ibọriṣa pẹlu.
english_text: 8 Loyalty to Jehovah also makes usguard againstidolatry.

yoruba_text: Ṣọrafun Awọn Ẹgbẹ́ Buburu
english_text: Guard Against Bad Associations

yoruba_text: A lè gbadura pẹlu iru awọn ẹni bẹẹ, kawe fun wọn, tabi sọ awọn iriri; ṣugbọn a nilatiṣọraki a má ṣe pẹ́ ju bi ara wọn ti lè gbàá lọ.
english_text: We can pray with such ones, read to them, or relate experiences; but we should becarefulnot to stay longer than they can handle.

yoruba_text: (Iṣe 12:21-23) Ó dara ki aṣọra, ki a pinnu lati ṣà wárí ki a sì jọsin ki ki Ọlọrun to otọ naa, ẹni ti “kò jinna si olukuluku wa” niti gidi.—Iṣe 17:27.
english_text: (Acts 12:21-23) We do well to keep onguard, resolved to seek out and worship only the true God, who really “is not far off from each one of us.” —Acts 17:27.

yoruba_text: Iwọ yoo fun Jehofa ni ifọkansin ti a yasọtọ gédégbé, oun yoo sì ràn ọ́ lọwọ lati maaṣọrafun gbogbo oniruuru ibọriṣa.
english_text: You will give Jehovah exclusive devotion, and he will help you to keep onguard againstidolatry of every sort.

yoruba_text: Lati ṣe iyẹn, iranṣẹ Ọlọrun gbọdọṣọralodisi jijẹ ẹni ti a danwo lati lọ rekọja à à là ominira Kristẹni.
english_text: To do that, a servant of God mustguardagainst being tempted to go beyond the limits of Christian freedom.

yoruba_text: Nigba wo ni awọn Kristian nilatiṣọrani pataki lati rìn pẹlu ọgbọ́n sipa awọn wọnni ti wọn wà lóde?
english_text: When should Christians be particularlycarefulto walk in wisdom toward those on the outside?

yoruba_text: Idi niyẹn ti Paulu fi ki lọ pe: “Ẹṣọra,... ki ẹnikankan ninu yin má baa di alá yà-líle nipa agbara ẹ̀tàn ẹṣẹ.”
english_text: That is why Paul warned: “Beware... for fear any one of you should become hardened by the deceptive power of sin.”

yoruba_text: ▫ Eeṣe ti awọn ọ̀dọ́ fi nilatiṣọranipa iru awọn orin ti wọn ń tẹ́tí si?
english_text: ▫ Why should young people becarefulas to the kind of music they listen to?

yoruba_text: 19. (a) Ki ni awọn wọnni ti wọn pinnu lati ṣe ito lẹsẹẹsẹ ẹ̀kọ́ alá fikún nilatiṣọrafun?
english_text: 19. (a) What precautions should be taken by those who decide to takesupplementarycourses?

yoruba_text: Eeṣe ti awọn alagba fi gbọdọṣọralati lo ikora-ẹni-nijaanu nigba ti wọn ba nsọ asọye fun gbogbo eniyan?
english_text: Why must elders becarefulto exercise self-control when giving public talks?

yoruba_text: Ṣọrafun ririn ni igun ẹba ọna, paapaa julọ bi o ba gbe iru apoti ẹru tabi apo eyi keyii dani.
english_text: Becautiousabout walking right along the edge of a sidewalk, especially if you are carrying a briefcase or a bag.

yoruba_text: Lọna ti o farajọra, ki koriira iwa-ailofin yoo mú waṣọralodisi gbogbo orin ti ń ru ifẹkufẹẹ soke ninu awọn ọ̀rọ̀ orin tabi dídún rẹ̀.
english_text: Similarly, hating lawlessness will make usguardagainst all music that is passion-arousing in its lyrics or its tempo.

yoruba_text: Awọn ètekéte tabi “awọn ìṣe alá rèékérekè” rẹ̀, ń dọdẹ mu awọn Kristian ti wọn kòṣọralọdọọdun.
english_text: His machinations, or “crafty acts,” are ensnaringunwary Christians every year.

yoruba_text: □ Bawo ni a ṣe lèṣọrafun isọra-ẹni di oriṣa?
english_text: □ How can weguardagainst self-idolatry?

yoruba_text: 6. (a) Eeṣe ti awọn èwe fi nilatiṣọranipa iru orin ti wọn yoo yàn?
english_text: 6. (a) Why do youths need to becautiousin their choice of music?

yoruba_text: Ṣugbọn ti o ba ti dariji ẹnikeji rẹ,ṣọrafun jíjẹ́ ki ìkannú ti kò tán nilẹ bọ̀rọ̀ ba rere ti o ti rígbà nipasẹ iṣe idariji jẹ́.
english_text: But if you have forgiven your mate, guard againstletting a lingering indignation undo the good that you achieved through the act of forgiveness.

yoruba_text: O ṣe pataki latiṣọralodisi mimu ẹmi irahun dagba.
english_text: It is important toguardagainst developing a complaining spirit.
